caption: Today i tried this new place for a quick lunch stop. i can say not bad at all it reminds me a restaurant in FL.We eat there all the time

Love the vibe and ambiance, particularly with the music and decor while sitting outside. Our server was really fun and nice. The food was good, and the cocktails were great! Loved the tiki drink. For food I enjoyed the crab sando, the pork bao buns, cheesy corn, and the veg dumplings with a delicious citrus-y sauce. The ramen wasn't great, I would definitely skip that next time.

Essentially a Japanese tapas joint. It’s a fun atmosphere with accommodating eccentric staff. A lot of great options. The bao buns are great. When we went they were out of pork belly which is a huge bummer also how do you run out of such an essential item? Do not get the ramen it is extremely bland you are better off with literally anything else.

Best restaurant in the neighborhood, hands down. Small plates are the best move but no bad items on the menu (I’ve had probably 3/4 of the items by now). Favorite item is the Bao buns, if they have mushroom thats the best variety. You might end up staying and spending anywhere between $15 to $100+ especially if you get drinks (though they usually have free Sake). Great for groups where you can share plates and try several things. Staff is attentive and friendly, definitely make the place what it is. Table and wall art is cool too, especially if you like sailor moon. If you’re visiting or have lived here a while, can’t recommend anywhere in UWS more than Moonrise Izakaya.
Super nice staff, great food, fun menu (chicken parm bao!) Loved the cocktails, especially the passion fruit ones.

Wait staff have an overwhelming energy-it's not for everyone.The food is good but expensive. Also claims to be Japanese place run by Jewish people but has a lot of Chinese and Korean tastes/spices/seasonings/dishes which is peak cultural appropriation. 2/5 because the food tasted good, but they were not authentic at all. Ma Pao Tofu is a Chinese dish and they somehow made it very similar to a Korean tofu stew. And for the record, there's no eggplant or onion slices in ma pao tofu. Wish the chef would do their research on real Japanese food, or just call it an Asian fusion place instead.

I mean, look. How many times do you find a place that is more interesting than the person you brought with you? Do you remember when New York was original? These folks do. If you and your wife Linda want to go somewhere joyless and discuss your finances over some tired Italian menu, I am happy for you. Moonrise will be here when you remember you’re alive!

Cool experience; but lacks some quality control with food and service. Well rounded food menu with an EXHAUSTIVE drink menu. Something for everyone here; with the sacrifice of service and them being out of many things. It’s understandable since the weather warmed up a bit, and dining is coming in a little more full swing since the pandemic. Hopefully they will improve on these fronts.  Food: 5/10 Food was mostly “alright” across the board. (Favorite to least favorite) Sticky rice, corned beef bao bun, shrimp dumplings, potato croquettes, mini ramen. Sticky rice was tasty but over cooked. The tempura fried rice was almost rock solid to where it wouldn’t be chewable, however the spicy tuna moistened it up. Mini ramen was bland, and tasted like the burnt ends of the pork from the dirty grill. Croquettes were the only thing that came out hot, and even then they were only good because they had both eel sauce and spicy mayo drizzled (instant red flag at ‘japanese’ restaurants).  Menu: 5/5 Expansive, a great mix of everything. Mostly small plates with some large plate options. Variety of proteins and plenty of interesting dishes to try out and share. The drink menu is ridiculous. They kill it on that point alone.  Value: 3/5 Food is fairly priced, smaller portions but slightly better than what you typically get at boutique type restaurants. Drinks are pretty PAR with the rest of Manhattan, although they do have a happy hour which knocks this to above average.  Experience: 3/5 Bailey was a phenomenal server; despite the service being spotty at first. This was due to the restaurant getting slammed at once. I think the venue will be able to iron out their service a bit as the weather warms up. Plenty of outdoor seating, heating options in the street seating. Some tables lacking menu QR code is annoying.  There is a bike lane going through the outdoor sidewalk seating and street seating, all i could think about is how many people have been taken out.
Good food. Pleasant staff.

Very well kept and welcoming place. They provide big portions and for economical prices. We enjoyed the menu a lot and the staff were very welcoming and explanatory. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.

Came here for brunch a few weeks ago in 40 degree weather. Due to indoor dining being closed, we were seated outdoors. Unfortunately when I went, they did not have heating, so it was a bit chilly while we waited for our food.  Booked this place through Resy, the check in was fairly simple and we were seated right away. We ordered a series of different dishes, both from the brunch and dinner menu and were given a free complimentary sake shot. We ordered the soft shell crab sandwich, pork belly Bao buns, matcha waffles with chicken kaarage (The Panda Combo), cheesy corn, sweet potato avocado toast, and the matcha swirl cheesecake. Due to the amount of people eating there, our food did take a while (about 40 minutes I would say) to come out. I was a bit disappointed when my Panda combo came out as my chicken kaarage was forgotten. Everyone else who had their food, enjoyed their meal.  By the time my kaarage came out, I had already finished my matcha waffles as I was starving and did not want cold waffles. Individually, the matcha waffles were amazing, and you can taste the earthy matcha flavor (I have not been able to achieve that when I make my own matcha waffles), and the kaarage was tasty though a little too salty. I can only imagine the combination together, I think the waffle and syrup would have cancelled out the saltiness of the kaarage.  Aside for the matcha waffles, another highlight was the matcha swirl cheesecake. Not only was it beautiful that we almost did not want to eat it, it was light and creamy as well.  Price wise, I would say it is average ($7-$20), as it is located in Manhattan. Service wise, the waiters were really chill and down to earth. Unfortunately we were seated around the corner, so it was hard to get their attention without having to get up.

Went there for dinner on a cold Saturday evening. First off, the server was really good, very attentive and friendly. The drinks are pretty good and unique. The warm Sweater Weather cocktail definitely helped in the freezing cold. The Bao Buns are average, the dumplings are fresh and tasty. But the negative of all this is they do not have a proper outdoor heated seating if you are party of 2 or more. They have an enclosed heated patio which was only restricted to party of two which I think was unfair coz it was almost empty the whole time we were there. So it was possible to socially distance as well as help customers from the cold.
Staff are very friendly.  Food is above average.
Oh my gosh! Loved everything about this place the drinks and food were amazing.
Very friendly and homely feeling, the food is prepared fresh, on every order. The staff is well informed of everything on the menu and I very professional and courteous.

Seemed like the hippest & hottest bar/restaurant in the neighborhood. A dozen people were sitting at outside tables in 45 deg. weather, on the sidewalk & in their wooden shelter. I ordered takeout, which was very good.
Soft shell crab sando was amazing. Everything bagel martini was really interesting
Amazing!
FANTASTIC food and an even better atmosphere. The staff is friendly and attentive, too! I highly recommend this restraurant to anyone craving a great time on the UWS.
Amazing gem on the UWS! Charismatic staff who serve delicious drinks and food

First of all, love the food since the first time we tried it. We ended up ordering one time through Uber eats and through some glitch or miscommunication, more than half our order was missing upon delivery. We called the restaurant up and the manager at the time remade all of our food, delivered it himself and waived the difference. Definitely will be returning there soon! Highly recommend.
Had a great experience. They took great care of our table.
Great food, great service and quirky cool atmosphere.
Good service but was was poorly executed and not so tasty. Felt cheap and not so well thought out
This place has such good food and drinks. Definitely recommend happy hour, even better deals!
Excellent service made all the difference! Bailey was fantastic!  They were out of a few items, but they totally made up for the quick service and warm hospitality. Total recommend!
Maybe its a Google issue, but if I click on a menu button I'd hope to see an actual menu, not random photos
the food is awesome and the staff went above and beyond to make sure we got our food properly ❤️
Incredible staff and very good food. Worth trying their Sake,

The best!
Great servers and large terrace during covid-19 times. Food was delicious.
Amazing as usual!
Cool place, food is good but not amazing
Lacking some of the izakaya standards but decent.
Excellent staff. Excellent food

the service was awful from the beginning but real mess started when we got to the payment point. We asked a waiter to split our check. It took him a couple of attempts, he had to redo it twice. And a cherry on a top - when I got my credit card statement I saw that they charged me twice. I disputed these charges with my credit card. In response to the dispute Moonrise Izakaya sent copies of "my" receipts - one of them was signed be me but another one was obviously signed by somebody else. And they did not hesitate to provide it as a proof of "my" payment! Absolutely shameless.
We had an amazing meal here, made me feel like we weren't in the middle of a pandemic! The food was incredible.
awesome place in the "new normal" everything we had was scrumptious
Fun place. Good, interesting menu - both in food and drinks. Service was friendly and fast. And they gave us a free sample of house saki!
Fun, good food, nice people, & lots of outdoor tables.
Great food for dine in or take out! Best customer service, the owner Jake goes above and beyond! Can’t wait for my next visit!
Best Bao Buns I have ever had!
The worst staff I have ever encountered at a food establishment One man was physically vulgar (purple hair streak), while a woman in braids berated me for no reason. Horrific.
Recently visited this location really stylish and friendly staff only wish they had more food options but I'll visit again
Though service is a bit slow, they are nice about it.. food and drinks are great reason to come back
Fun sake bar

New in our neighborhood, so we had to go. The kids and I loved it. Had the blistered shishito peppers and the mall tofu and the seafood pancake and one of the beef ramen dishes. Packed on a Friday night. Readily friendly staff. We were in and out in an hour. Reservations recommended.

Great atmosphere with lots of excellent food choices and live music. I went on my birthday after seeing the ballet and it was the perfect end to the night. Get the monkfish goujons they were my favourite!
Cool vibe, tasty menu options with decent portions size, which is all that matters.
Very nice place. Chicken wings are amazing.
Food is excellent here- highly recommend the pork bao bun! The sake menu was also one of the better sake menus I've seen in NYC! This place is a must go!
Bomb food and great service. It’s a really nice vibe; glad this place popped up in the neighborhood!
So yummy. And a great ambiance. This is my new neighborhood place!  I particularly love the agedashi tofu which is really authentic.
Great atmosphere and amazing food!
Great food and great prices. I will definitely return.
Had a great time at this new UWS Izakaya restaurant. Saki was flowing, service was great, and the food was superb. I highly recommend this place!
Tasty food, cool vibe, friendly service

I’ve been here a bunch of times since it opened. The food is delicious and affordable and everything tastes good on the menu so I keep going back to try different things.  The cheesy corn is a crowd pleaser. Every time I go I always order the fried chicken and the sausage and the agedashi tofu is super addictive. I love the seafood pancake too. Even the sashimi platter has generous slices of fish and tastes fresh. I keep rotating through the other items like pork and fried chicken bao buns and I heard from someone else that the cheeseburger is delicious so I definitely want to get that next time I go. Right now they have matcha cheesecake but I heard soon there’s going to be tempura ice cream and mochi ice cream I can’t wait.
Great food! Highly recommend going
Great food, Great Sake and Great Time is the only way to explain the new Upper West Side gem.
Great food & sake selection!
Great spot to hang out with a few friends for a few drinks and some good food. Jake and David have created a fun relaxed environment with a great staff
